The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery from incomplete measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The use of restricted isometry property and mutual coherence also suggests a connection to compressed sensing, which is a subfield of both information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.SP are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
